Step1: 
I structured my repository using a reproducible bioinformatics workflow. I separated notebooks, scripts, data documentation, and results to make the analysis easier to maintain and reproduce.

Step2: Biology Foundation: PBMC 3k Dataset
Learned:
- PBMC stands for Peripheral Blood Mononuclear Cells
- The dataset contains immune cells from human blood
- Single-cell RNA-seq measures gene expression at the individual cell level
- The goal is to identify cell populations based on gene expression patterns

Interview Explanation:
"This project analyzes single-cell RNA-seq data from PBMCs to identify immune cell populations based on gene expression patterns. I use Scanpy to perform quality control, dimensionality reduction, clustering, and visualization."
